Woe to those who sin and do not repent, for the day of judgment is near and there will be no mercy for them. The fire is kindled and the earth shall be shaken. The sword of YHWH is drawn and it shall not return until it has consumed the wicked. Therefore prepare your souls and turn to the Most High while there is still time.
The end draws near. The books are opened and every deed is recorded. The righteous shall be saved but the ungodly shall perish. The trumpet sounds and the dead arise. The Son of Man comes in glory with all His holy ones. Then the judgment is set and the books are opened.
Behold the days come when the Most High will deliver those who are on the earth. The earth shall tremble and the foundations of the sea shall be shaken. The fire shall not be quenched and the sword shall not cease until it has consumed the wicked. Woe to the world and those who dwell in it for the sword and fire are near.
The Most High has spoken: “Behold the days come when I will visit the inhabitants of the earth. The innocent blood cries out and the earth shall no longer hide it. The time of threshing has come and the harvest is ripe. The evil shall be cut off and the righteous shall be gathered.”
