CH14

And it came to pass, when the forty days were fulfilled, that the Most High took Ezra from among men and carried him up to heaven, where he was with the Anointed until the times should be fulfilled. And the people saw him no more.
And Ezra wrote all these things and taught them publicly to the people. And he delivered the twenty-four books to the people, but the seventy secret books he kept for the wise among them.
Then the Most High spoke to Ezra saying: “Publish the twenty-four books that you have written first, that the worthy and unworthy may read them. But keep the seventy last books for the wise among your people, for in them is the spring of understanding, the fountain of wisdom, and the river of knowledge.”
And Ezra drank from the cup of fire and his heart poured forth understanding. And wisdom increased in him, and his mouth was opened and was no longer closed. And the Most High gave him understanding, and he wrote day and night the things that were told him.
And the Most High said to Ezra: “Go and gather the people and tell them not to seek you for forty days. And you shall prepare many boxes and take with you Sarea, Dabria, Selemia, Ecanus, and Asiel, these five who are ready to write swiftly. And you shall come here, and I will light a lamp of understanding in your heart which shall not be put out until you have finished writing what I command you.”

CH13

And the Most High said to Ezra: “This is the interpretation of the vision: The man who came up from the sea is he whom the Most High has kept for many ages, who by his own hand will deliver his creation. He is the Anointed whom the Most High has reserved until the end of days. The mountain upon which he stood is Mount Zion. The multitude that gathered against him are the nations that will come against him in the last days. The fire that came out of his mouth and consumed them is the word of judgment that will destroy them. The storm that came from his mouth is the breath of the Anointed that will burn them up. The great peace that followed is the rest that the Most High will give to his people. This is the interpretation of the vision you have seen.”
And after this I looked, and behold, a multitude of men without number gathered from the four winds of heaven to make war against the man who came up from the sea. And when they saw him, they were greatly afraid and fell upon their faces. But he took the mountain and stood upon it. And when the multitude saw him standing upon the mountain, they all gathered together to fight against him. And he sent forth from his mouth as it were a stream of fire, and from his lips a flaming breath, and from his tongue a storm of sparks. And all these things — the stream of fire, the flaming breath, and the storm of sparks — fell upon the multitude that was prepared to fight and burned them all up, so that suddenly nothing was seen of the innumerable multitude except dust of ashes and the smell of smoke.
And after this I saw, and behold, a man came up from the heart of the sea. And he flew with the clouds of heaven. And wherever he turned his face to look, everything that looked at him trembled. And whenever his voice spoke, all who heard his voice melted as wax melts before the fire.

CH12

And the lion whom you saw rousing up out of the forest and roaring and speaking to the eagle and rebuking him for his unrighteousness, this is the Anointed whom the Most High has kept until the end of days, who shall spring from the seed of David. He shall reprove them for their wickedness and their evil deeds, and shall set them before the judgment seat. He shall destroy them and deliver the remnant of my people, those who have been saved throughout my borders, and he shall make them joyful until the end comes, the day of judgment, of which I spoke to you from the beginning.
This is the interpretation of the vision which you have seen. As for the lion which you saw coming up out of the forest and roaring and speaking to the eagle and reproving him for his unrighteousness, this is the Anointed whom the Most High has kept until the end of days. He shall set them before the judgment seat and shall reprove them for their wickedness and their evil deeds. He shall deliver the remnant of my people and make them joyful until the end comes, the day of judgment.
And it came to pass, while I was speaking these words to the angel, that he said to me: “Rise up, Ezra, and hear the words which I have come to speak to you.” And I said: “Speak, my Lord.” And he said to me: “The eagle which you saw coming up from the sea is the fourth kingdom which appeared to your brother Daniel in a vision. But it was not explained to him as I now explain it to you. The days are coming when a kingdom shall arise which shall be more terrible than all that were before it. And twelve kings shall reign in it, one after another. But the second shall begin to reign, and shall have a longer reign than any of the twelve. This is the interpretation of the twelve wings which you saw.”
And the angel said to me: “The eagle which you saw coming up from the sea is the fourth kingdom which appeared in a vision to your brother Daniel. But it was not explained to him as I now explain it or have explained it to you.”

