And it came to pass, while I was speaking these words to the angel, that he said to me: “Rise up, Ezra, and hear the words which I have come to speak to you.” And I said: “Speak, my Lord.” And he said to me: “The eagle which you saw coming up from the sea is the fourth kingdom which appeared to your brother Daniel in a vision.”
And behold, a voice was heard from heaven saying: “Hear, O earth, the words of the Most High. Behold, the days come when I will visit the inhabitants of the earth. The innocent blood cries out and the earth shall no longer hide it. The time of threshing has come and the harvest is ripe.”
And after this I looked, and behold, an eagle came up from the sea and had twelve feathered wings and three heads. And I saw, and behold, it spread its wings over all the earth and all the winds of heaven blew upon it. And the clouds were gathered together against it and the earth was afraid. And I saw that all things under heaven were subject to it. And I saw that from its wings there grew other little wings, and they became small and feeble wings. And the heads rested, and the middle head which was greater than the others was lifted up. And I saw that the eagle flew with its wings and reigned over the earth and over those who dwell in it. And I saw that the earth was quiet and still. And the eagle arose upon its talons and its voice was heard. And it spoke with a loud voice saying: “Hear me, you who dwell on the earth. I have reigned over the earth and I have delivered it from all evil. But now the time of my end has come and I must depart. Therefore choose for yourselves a ruler who will govern you in my place.” And it spoke these words and its heads were at rest. And the middle head suddenly disappeared. And the two remaining heads turned and devoured each other. And the whole body of the eagle was burned and the earth was in great fear.

CH10

The angel said to me: “This woman whom you saw is Zion. The woman who appeared to you in the beginning as a city built is the heavenly Jerusalem which is now invisible. The son whom she bore is the Messiah who will come and deliver his people. The sorrow and mourning you saw is the desolation of Zion. The transformation you witnessed is the restoration that will come when the Most High visits his people.”
And the woman said to me: “I am your mother Zion. I have been desolate and in great sorrow because my son has died. But now the Most High has comforted me and shown me his glory.” And as I looked, the woman’s face shone like the sun and her form became a great city with strong foundations. And I was afraid and cried out to the angel.
Then the woman began to speak to me with a loud voice and said: “Why are you so troubled? Why is your face so changed?” And I said to her: “Because I am greatly grieved in my heart and my spirit is troubled.” And she said to me: “You are grieved for Zion. I am your mother Zion who has been barren and in great sorrow. But now the Most High has remembered me and has shown me his glory.”
And while I was speaking these words with the woman, her face suddenly shone exceedingly and her form became like lightning. And I was very afraid and fell upon my face. And I heard a voice from heaven saying: “Ezra, do not be afraid. This is the interpretation of the vision.”
And the angel who had been sent to me took me by the right hand and strengthened me and set me upon my feet. And he said to me: “Stand up like a man and I will explain the vision to you.”
And as I was speaking with her, her face suddenly shone exceedingly and her form became like lightning. And I was very afraid and fell upon my face. And I heard a voice from heaven saying: “Ezra, do not be afraid. This is the interpretation of the vision.”
And the woman began to speak to me with a loud voice and said: “Why are you so troubled? Why is your face so changed?” And I said to her: “Because I am greatly grieved in my heart and my spirit is troubled.” And she said to me: “You are grieved for Zion. I am your mother Zion who has been barren and in great sorrow. But now the Most High has remembered me and has shown me his glory.”

CH9

The angel answered and said to me: “The Most High has revealed these things to you because you are righteous before Him. The signs you have seen are the beginning of the sorrows. When you see these things, know that the end is near. The time is divided: the first half has passed, and the latter half remains. The age is hastening to its end like a ship driven by the wind. The books are opened and the judgment is at hand. Therefore prepare your soul and turn to the Most High while there is still time.”
And the angel said to me: “You are more blessed than many, for you have been called to understand these things. The Most High has shown you the end of the times and the beginning of the new age. Keep these words in your heart and teach them to the wise among your people.”
Then the angel said to me: “Rise up, Ezra, and stand upon your feet. I have been sent to show you these things and to interpret the vision for you. The woman you saw is Zion, the heavenly Jerusalem. Her sorrow is the desolation of the city, and her transformation is the glory that is to come. The son she bore is the Messiah who will deliver his people.”
And as I was speaking these words, the angel who was talking with me said to me: “Do not be afraid, Ezra. The Most High has shown you these things because you are dear to Him. The vision you have seen is true, and its interpretation is certain.”
And the angel answered me and said: “The Most High has revealed these mysteries to you because you have found favor before Him. These signs are the beginning of the end. When you see them, know that the time is near.”
And after this I wept bitterly and my heart was troubled within me. And I said to the angel: “Why have I been born to see the desolation of my people and the affliction of my race? Why have I been made to see the destruction of Zion and the ruin of the sanctuary?”

CH8

The angel answered and said to me: “The Most High has made this world for the sake of many, but the world to come for the sake of few. Many have been created, but few shall be saved.”
And I answered and said: “If I have found favor in your sight, show me this also: whether the righteous will be able to intercede for the ungodly on the day of judgment — whether fathers for sons, or sons for fathers, or brothers for brothers, or kinsmen for their nearest kin, or friends for those dearest to them.”
The angel said: “You are greatly troubled in mind for the sake of the world. Will you be greatly grieved for the sake of the perishing? For the day of judgment is decisive. It displays to all the seal of truth. In that day no one will be able to save one who has been condemned, nor to condemn one who has been acquitted.”
Then the angel said to me: “The Most High has made this age for the sake of many, but the age to come for the sake of few. Many have been created, but few shall be saved. Many are created, but few are chosen.”
And I answered and said: “Then, O Lord, why have you made all this? Why have you not made all men righteous at once? Why have you not created them all at once? Why have you not shown your judgment at once?”
The angel answered me and said: “The Most High has made this world for the sake of many, but the world to come for the sake of few. Many have been created, but few shall be saved.”
Then I answered and said: “O Lord who bears rule, if I have found favor in your sight, show me this also: whether we shall be kept in the world after death, or whether we shall be tormented at once.”
And the angel answered and said: “The Most High has made this world for the sake of many, but the world to come for the sake of few. Many have been created, but few shall be saved.”

