CH3

Then the angel Uriel was sent to me and said: “Your heart is troubled beyond measure concerning the ways of the Most High. You seek to understand what is above your understanding. The ways of the Most High are not to be searched out by man. The earth is given to the wicked for a little while, but the righteous shall inherit the world to come. Be patient therefore and wait for the fulfillment of the times.”
And I answered and said: “O Lord, why have You given the power to Babylon to rule over Your people? Why have You allowed the wicked to prosper while Your chosen ones are afflicted? Have the deeds of those who inhabit Babylon been better than those of Israel? Or have You utterly rejected Your people?”
In the thirtieth year after the destruction of the city I was in Babylon, and I was troubled as I lay on my bed, and my thoughts were raised up in my heart. For I saw the desolation of Zion and the wealth of those who lived in Babylon. And my spirit was greatly agitated, and I began to speak anxious words to the Most High.

CH2

Thus says the Lord to Ezra: “Proclaim these words in the midst of my people. Tell them that I will gather them from the four corners of the earth and bring them to the eternal kingdom. Those who have kept my commandments shall inherit the land, but those who have forsaken me shall be cast out. The mother who has many children shall be desolate, but the barren one shall rejoice. The day of judgment is near and the books shall be opened.”
And the Most High said to me: “Go and tell my people that I will give them the kingdom of Jerusalem which I was going to give to Israel. I will take away their glory and give it to others. I will scatter them among the nations and they shall be a proverb and a byword. But I will not forsake them forever. In the last days I will remember them and gather them from the ends of the earth.”
Thus says the Lord: “I brought you out of Egypt and led you through the wilderness for forty years. I gave you leaders, priests, and prophets. But you rebelled against me and turned to idols. Therefore I have rejected you and given your heritage to others. Yet I will not utterly cast you off. In the last days I will remember the covenant and gather you again.”
And the Most High said to me: “Proclaim these words among my people. Tell them I will gather them from the four winds and bring them to the eternal Jerusalem. Those who have kept my law shall inherit the kingdom, but those who have rejected me shall be cast into outer darkness.”

CH1

Therefore the Most High has rejected you and given your heritage to others. He has scattered you among the nations and you have become a proverb and a byword. Yet I will not utterly cast you off forever. In the last days I will remember the covenant of your fathers and gather you again from the four corners of the earth.
Thus says the Lord who brought you out of Egypt and led you through the wilderness for forty years. I gave you leaders, priests, and prophets. I sent my servants the prophets to you, but you persecuted and killed them. You turned to idols and forsook my commandments. Therefore I have rejected you and scattered you among the nations.
In the thirtieth year after the destruction of the city I was in Babylon, and I was troubled as I lay on my bed, and my thoughts were raised up in my heart. For I saw the desolation of Zion and the wealth of those who lived in Babylon. And my spirit was greatly agitated, and I began to speak anxious words to the Most High.
The word of the Lord came to me, Ezra, saying: “Go and declare to my people their sins and transgressions. Tell them how I brought them out of Egypt with a mighty hand and led them through the wilderness. I gave them my law and my statutes, but they rebelled against me and turned to idols. Therefore I have rejected them and given their heritage to others.”

